1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,456
The major adverse cardiac outcomes fall into

2
00:00:03,456 --> 00:00:04,444
four domains.

3
00:00:04,444 --> 00:00:07,900
First, left ventricular dysfunction and cardiogenic shock

4
00:00:07,900 --> 00:00:10,863
— often requiring mechanical circulatory support.

5
00:00:10,863 --> 00:00:14,319
Second, ventricular arrhythmias — including VT and

6
00:00:14,319 --> 00:00:17,775
VF — mechanistically linked to myocyte edema,

7
00:00:17,775 --> 00:00:21,231
gap junction dysfunction, and abnormal calcium handling.

8
00:00:21,231 --> 00:00:24,688
Third, bradyarrhythmias — high-grade AV block necessitating

9
00:00:24,688 --> 00:00:25,675
temporary pacing.

10
00:00:25,675 --> 00:00:29,131
Fourth, thromboembolic events including stroke, driven by

11
00:00:29,131 --> 00:00:31,600
stasis from left ventricular dysfunction.
